io: rename UNION members and move AT pragma to unblock analog input tests

Root cause of the long-standing FB_AnalogInput test-project build break:
TwinCAT's compiler mis-parses UNION members with 1-character identifiers
(`r : REAL;`, `i : INT;`) when the enclosing FB is extended by a subclass
in a referenced library. Every attempt to `FUNCTION_BLOCK
FB_AnalogInput_Probe EXTENDS TcForge.FB_AnalogInput` produced cascading
C0009 / C0189 / C0004 errors pinned to the UNION member lines.

Fix:
- Rename U_IoRaw_In / U_IoRaw_Out members: r -> fReal, i -> nInt.
- Move AT %I* / AT %Q* from the UNION member onto the enclosing
  ST_AnalogInput_IO.inRaw / ST_AnalogOutput_IO.outRaw variable (DMC
  documented pattern). Hardware-link syntax on `.dw` is unchanged.
- Update FB_AnalogInput / FB_AnalogOutput call sites.

Result: Testing project now inherits FB_AnalogInput cleanly, so the
full 12-case FB_AnalogInput_Test suite covers the conditioning pipeline
end-to-end (initial status, linear scaling, raw bypass, clamp-low/high,
CLAMPED quality promotion, cfgClampAsFault -> ClampLow/ClampHigh faults,
BadConfig first-scan, BAD-quality LKG hold, TYPE_REAL UNION member read,
quality-tag propagation).

Full suite: 118 tests across 12 suites, green on 172.18.236.100.1.1.
